Russian Ambassador Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Valery E. Sukhinin Wednesday hosted a reception at his embassy on the occasion of Kim Jong Il's birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Kim Yong Chun, vice-chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, Pak Ui Chun, minister of Foreign Affairs, Pak Kyong Son, vice department director of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Pak Jae Gyong, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were staff members of the Russian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Valery E. Sukhinin in his speech said that Kim Jong Il is widely known as an outstanding politician, the leader of the Korean Party, army and people and a friend of the Russian people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that this year marks the 60th anniversary of the DPRK, he wished the Korean people greater success in building a great prosperous powerful nation and bolstering the defence capability of the country under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Chun, addressing the reception, noted that Kim Jong Il has performed great feats on behalf of the era and history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He recalled that the DPRK-Russia relations have favorably developed in various fields as required by the spirit of the joint agreements reached at the meetings between Kim Jong Il and President Putin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that to set store by the traditional DPRK-Russia friendship and steadily boost it is in line with the desire and interests of the peoples of the two countries and consistent is the DPRK's stand on the DPRK-Russia relations, he wished the Russian people prosperity and well-being.

Japan's Building of Missile Shield under Fire  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- Recently the Japanese military deployed PAC-3s in the area south-west of Tokyo. Earlier, the military deployed missile defence installations made up of launching pad and radar in two bases around Tokyo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The criminal scenario of the Japanese militarist forces is being translated into a reality as evidenced by the facts that Aegis destroyer "Kongo" of the Japan Maritime "Self-Defence Force" was deployed at the Sasebo base close to the DPRK to be ready to go into action after conducting its first test-fire of interceptor missile in the waters off Hawaii at the outset of this year and they announced a plan to increase the number of Aegis ships equipped with interceptor missiles to four. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today observes in a signed commentary carried in this connection: The Japanese reactionaries' moves to build missile shields reveal a very dangerous plan for reinvasion which should not be overlooked. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is the scenario of the Japanese reactionaries to cover their islands with a dense network of missiles and use them for making preemptive strikes at the DPRK any time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tokyo Metropolitan governor Ishihara, a militarist fanatic, recently cried out for deploying a PAC-3 in the plaza of the "Imperial Palace" of Japan to make the people feel "danger." This is little short of adding fuel to the fire. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As for Ishihara, he is an icon of the ultra-right forces and a war maniac as he is steeped in bitterness toward the DPRK and chauvinism to the marrow of his bones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His recent remarks represent the Japanese reactionaries' undisguised agitation for staging a comeback to Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are pushing the DPRK-Japan hostile relations to the lowest ebb, while stepping up their moves to round off the preparations for launching reinvasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Their extreme hostile policy toward the DPRK is heightening the hatred of the army and the people of the DPRK toward Japan. Should the Japanese reactionaries persist in their moves for reinvasion, accelerating the building of missile shields targeted against the DPRK, this will entail catastrophic consequences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries would be well advised to bear this in mind and stop their rash actions.

Stronger Forces for Peaceful Reunification Called for in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- The Citizens' Solidarity for Peaceful Reunification of south Korea reportedly held a general meeting in Seoul on Feb. 15 at which it called for strengthening the forces for peaceful reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization noted that it is the core task before the progressive camp to defend the democratic right gained at the cost of the blood and sweat of the people and successes made by the south and the north in the reunification movement and strengthen the broad forces for peaceful reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called on the organizations of the reunification movement from various circles to firmly unite and make positive contributions to achieving the peaceful reunification of the Korean peninsula under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration so as to hand a reunified country down to posterity.

U.S. Deployment of "Striker" Unit in S. Korea under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists reportedly deployed the "Striker" unit, a rapid task force, in Taegu of south Korea on Feb. 15. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. forces side in south Korea said that the above-said unit would take part in the joint military exercises codenamed "Key Resolve-Eagle 08" to be staged in south Korea in early March. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unit is expected to stage a live shell firing drill prior to the start of the war exercises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unit which the U.S. imperialist warmongers advertised as a "model of the ground forces in the 21st century" took part in a series of war exercises targeted against the DPRK, bringing the situation on the Korean Peninsula to an extreme pitch of tension. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists would be well advised to properly understand the Korean nation's will for independence and peaceful reunification and cancel at once their plan for staging dangerous saber rattling against the DPRK, while talking about dialogue and negotiations.

Kim Jong Il�fs Birthday Observed in Foreign Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- Seminars and film shows were held in Romania, Mexico and Guyana during the period from January 29 to February 6 on the occasion of the birthday of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the events were personages of different social standings, members of the preparatory committees for celebrating February 16, groups for the study of the Juche idea and organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people and other people of the above-said countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the film shows watched "They Are Together on the Way of Great Songun Leadership" and "The 75th Anniversary of the Heroic Korean People's Army" and other Korean films. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Daniel Dediu, chairman of the Romanian Workers' Association, in his speech highly praised Kim Jong Il for having victoriously led the Korean revolution holding higher the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ramon Jimenez Lopez, president of the Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism, in his speech declared the members of the committee would intensify the study and dissemination of the Songun idea and the Songun politics, noting that the Songun idea and the Songun politics are commanding stronger support and sympathy from the world progressives day by day.

Exploits of Kim Jong Il Praised by Foreign Personages 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- Sekou Konate, general secretary of the Party for Unity and Progress of Guinea, and Saber Ballul, department head of the Political Faculty of University of Damascus of Syria, separately released statements praising the exploits of Kim Jong Il on the occasion of his birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sekou Konate in his statement on February 13 said that Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, is the great statesman who has victoriously led the Korean revolution with the Songun idea and single-minded unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il is the matchless great master of politics and the great leader who clearly indicated the way to be followed by the peoples of the developing countries as he has pursued the Songun politics firmly defending the sovereignty of the country and the destiny of the people in any adversity and providing a guarantee for the prosperity of the country and the happy life of the people, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saber Ballul in his statement on February 11 noted that Kim Jong Il has successfully carried forward the cause of President Kim Il Sung after his demise, lauding him as a prominent statesman possessed of iron-will and noble personality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is outstanding among his exploits is that he has pursued the Songun politics, the best one meeting requirements of the developing situation, he said, adding that thanks to the Songun politics the DPRK emerged a military power strong enough to wipe out any formidable enemy.
